SIMPLE: scurrilous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scurrilous
<hw>Scur"ril*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<ets>Scurrile</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Using the low and indecent
language of the meaner sort of people, or such as only the license of
buffoons can warrant; <as>as, a <ex>scurrilous</ex>
fellow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Containing low indecency or abuse; mean; foul; vile;
obscenely jocular; <as>as, <ex>scurrilous</ex> language</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The absurd and <qex>scurrilous</qex> sermon which had very
unwisely been honored with impeachment.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Opprobrious; abusive; reproachful; insulting;
insolent; offensive; gross; vile; vulgar; low; foul; foul-mouthed;
indecent; scurrile; mean.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Scur"ril*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Scur"ril*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scurrit</ent>⟦br⟧
